{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow Community First Responders to use green strobe lights on their vehicles",
        "additional_details": "Community First Responders should be allowed to use green strobe lights on their vehicles when traveling to emergencies. These lights would enhance their visibility, alerting other drivers and pedestrians to their urgent mission. This increased awareness can help ensure a faster response time, ultimately saving lives.\r\n\r\nThe objective is not to demand priority or violate laws but to enhance visibility and signal their response to incidents authorized by Ambulance Service Control.",
        "background": "Community First Responders should be permitted to use green strobe lights or rotating beacons to indicate emergency calls and request courtesy. Legislative amendments are necessary to facilitate this.",
